<item>
            <title>[LU-15194] fix unusual readahead window behavior with single page reads</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-15194</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Readahead has a bit of odd behavior with single page reads.&#160; The first page read does not cause the readahead code to be called, so it doesn&apos;t learn the actual RPC size data.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;That means if the first read is a single page read and the next read triggers readahead, the size of the readahead is MAX_BRW_PAGES - so the readahead window is set to 64 MiB, even if the RPC size is set to 1 MiB or 4 MiB!&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
